WEBVTT

00:00.994 --> 00:04.118
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:04.699 --> 00:18.377
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:19.118 --> 00:26.668
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:26.708 --> 00:27.890
Today,

00:27.970 --> 00:35.982
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:39.328 --> 00:39.929
Peace be with you.

00:40.169 --> 00:43.855
Friends, for this Sunday, I want to talk to you once again about faith.

00:44.436 --> 00:51.947
I know I talk a lot about that, but as I've said before, it's the most misunderstood word in the religious vocabulary.

00:51.987 --> 00:53.810
So here I go again.

00:53.890 --> 01:01.482
Follow the Bible as it walks around this phenomenon of faith, because faith is so central, but also so misunderstood.

01:02.223 --> 01:07.311
In our time, the way it's most misunderstood is faith is a kind of superstition.

01:07.852 --> 01:11.357
Faith is a stupid acceptance of things on the basis of no evidence.

01:11.838 --> 01:13.741
Faith is believing in any old nonsense.

01:14.221 --> 01:16.345
That's not what faith means.

01:16.525 --> 01:17.947
It never means that in the Bible.

01:18.408 --> 01:22.354
That's the sort of modern rationalism that is caricatured

01:22.434 --> 01:23.615
religious faith.

01:23.635 --> 01:26.038
But look in the Bible as it talks about it a lot.

01:26.498 --> 01:29.041
It never, ever means that by faith.

01:29.722 --> 01:34.988
You know, whatever talks about Abraham, pay attention to those stories because Abraham is our father in faith.

01:35.528 --> 01:36.449
So those are always about it.

01:36.790 --> 01:45.479
Remember a few weeks ago, we had that wonderful passage from the letter to the Hebrews that talks about faith as a kind of pressing ahead toward things that we cannot see.

01:45.519 --> 01:48.542
It's a kind of spiritual adventure, right?

01:48.562 --> 01:51.986
Well, both reading one today and the gospel shed

01:52.098 --> 01:54.681
Very interesting light, I think, on the nature of faith.

01:55.422 --> 02:00.008
So reading one is from a little-known minor prophet called Habakkuk.

02:00.629 --> 02:05.335
Habakkuk is a wonderful figure, actually, and the book is brief, but really punching and interesting.

02:06.857 --> 02:08.339
Writing at a time, I'll simplify it.

02:08.659 --> 02:14.086
When Israel's going through a lot of struggle, the people are wondering what God is up to.

02:14.186 --> 02:15.107
Where is God?

02:15.668 --> 02:16.909
Listen now to this language.

02:17.550 --> 02:20.594
So he's channeling the voice of the people Israel.

02:21.762 --> 02:26.147
How long, O Lord, I cry for help, but you do not listen.

02:26.207 --> 02:30.591
I cry out to you violence, but you do not intervene.

02:31.572 --> 02:33.474
Why do you let me see ruin?

02:33.574 --> 02:35.176
Why must I look at misery?

02:35.596 --> 02:37.739
Destruction and violence are before me.

02:39.360 --> 02:40.141
That sound familiar?

02:40.742 --> 02:42.844
That's a credica, right?

02:42.864 --> 02:48.850
A cry of the heart that you could, almost any moment in human history, you could credibly hear that.

02:49.570 --> 02:51.873
How many times have we said that in our lives?

02:52.194 --> 02:53.275
Something's going wrong.

02:53.976 --> 02:58.382
We're going through times of great pain and suffering, failure, violence.

02:59.404 --> 03:00.465
Where are you, God?

03:00.886 --> 03:02.167
What's the problem?

03:02.227 --> 03:03.309
When are you coming?

03:03.850 --> 03:05.492
When are you going to keep your promise to us?

03:06.533 --> 03:10.178
So it wills naturally up out of the human heart, this kind of question.

03:12.041 --> 03:14.845
Well, where's it coming from, this sort of attitude?

03:15.486 --> 03:16.287
Can I suggest this?

03:17.569 --> 03:18.610
It's coming from

03:18.690 --> 03:28.062
the very narrow place, the very narrow compass of what we can understand and perceive.

03:29.383 --> 03:35.310
Think for a second, we have these bodies with this little sensarium of eyes and ears and so on.

03:36.071 --> 03:40.577
So we can take in what these senses are capable of taking in.

03:41.879 --> 03:47.986
Our minds can roam around reality, yeah, to some degree, but what we understand

03:48.290 --> 03:52.055
of the present much less the future, it's almost nothing.

03:52.916 --> 03:58.063
We have a little tiny swath of reality that we're able to control or understand.

03:58.103 --> 04:03.890
And so from that perspective, yes, we tend to say, what's going on?

04:04.210 --> 04:04.951
I don't get it.

04:05.933 --> 04:09.557
God exists, they tell me God exists, but it doesn't seem to be doing anything.

04:10.298 --> 04:16.306
Well, yeah, within this very, very narrow compass, think of,

04:16.578 --> 04:33.017
If a page of a great novel was ripped out and then it was thrown to the wind and then many months later, you happen to stumble upon the single page and you pick it up and it's an English and you can read it and it's given you a little tiny snippet of the story.

04:33.537 --> 04:37.402
But if you were to say, well, wherever that book comes from, it doesn't make a liquor sense.

04:38.243 --> 04:39.684
This book is ridiculous.

04:40.085 --> 04:44.530
Well, no, you're reading one page out of a thousand page story.

04:46.658 --> 04:48.280
See, what's required, everybody?

04:48.320 --> 04:49.941
Now we're going to shed some light on faith.

04:51.403 --> 05:01.713
What's required is a surrender in trust to God's perspective, God's plan, God's purpose.

05:03.214 --> 05:04.055
I can't see it.

05:04.235 --> 05:07.638
All I see is violence and destruction and you're not doing anything.

05:08.539 --> 05:09.240
Yeah, yeah, I know.

05:10.121 --> 05:10.361
I know.

05:10.401 --> 05:13.104
That's what you can see of my creation.

05:14.965 --> 05:15.666
Faith

05:16.866 --> 05:24.435
is an acceptance in humility and trust of God's vision plan purpose.

05:24.976 --> 05:31.484
Now, listen to how God answers this cry of heart that's in all of our hearts, listen.

05:33.146 --> 05:46.802
Then the Lord answered me and He said, write down the vision clearly upon the tablets so that one can read it readily, for the vision still has its time, presses on,

05:46.914 --> 05:49.257
to fulfillment and it will not disappoint.

05:49.317 --> 05:52.120
If it delays, wait for it.

05:52.580 --> 05:53.742
It will surely come.

05:53.782 --> 05:54.963
It will not be late.

05:56.024 --> 06:03.733
The rash one has no integrity, but the just one because of his faith will live.

06:04.955 --> 06:05.455
All right.

06:05.776 --> 06:07.798
So Lord, where are you?

06:08.739 --> 06:09.800
Doesn't make any sense.

06:11.843 --> 06:14.866
Have faith and it means what?

06:15.522 --> 06:19.468
that the vision has its time on God's time.

06:21.150 --> 06:22.372
God's work is being done.

06:22.512 --> 06:23.593
Trust in it.

06:24.775 --> 06:26.397
It presses on to fulfillment.

06:26.758 --> 06:30.663
Maybe you can't see how it's happening, but it's happening.

06:31.324 --> 06:32.766
It will not disappoint.

06:33.407 --> 06:35.650
God is never gonna give up on his creation.

06:35.670 --> 06:37.092
That's a basic biblical truth.

06:37.713 --> 06:40.617
God is not about a failed work.

06:41.298 --> 06:41.639
No, no.

06:42.600 --> 06:44.082
And if it delays,

06:44.546 --> 06:46.848
Yeah, from my perspective, it's delayed.

06:47.409 --> 06:48.049
I don't see it.

06:48.109 --> 06:49.110
I don't get it.

06:49.130 --> 06:50.732
If it delays, wait for it.

06:51.152 --> 06:52.133
See, what is that, everybody?

06:52.274 --> 06:53.735
That's the attitude of faith.

06:54.976 --> 06:58.039
Waiting and trust for what God will do.

06:58.059 --> 07:00.782
The rash one has no integrity.

07:01.002 --> 07:03.605
Well, that's most of us in our sin.

07:03.665 --> 07:05.066
I'm rash.

07:05.146 --> 07:06.187
I want an answer now.

07:06.808 --> 07:08.389
Put it to me on my terms.

07:08.930 --> 07:10.291
Well, that person has no integrity.

07:10.692 --> 07:13.234
But the just one,

07:14.050 --> 07:17.113
because of his faith will live.

07:18.174 --> 07:18.394
Right.

07:18.875 --> 07:28.444
How do we live spiritually by faith, by an attitude of humble trust in the ways of the Lord?

07:29.465 --> 07:31.688
Okay, that's Habakkuk reading number one.

07:32.168 --> 07:41.938
And it's preparing us for the gospel, which is to me really interesting text, the way it's pieced together.

07:42.018 --> 07:44.722
just before our gospel from Luke.

07:44.742 --> 07:49.209
What we have is Jesus' command to forgive extravagantly.

07:49.229 --> 07:54.698
You know, 70 times, seven times, forgive, forgive even your enemies, forgive, forgive.

07:55.639 --> 08:02.690
And the disciples, here's where our gospel today commences, disciples say to the Lord, increase our faith.

08:02.730 --> 08:07.698
They're saying, okay, I get the command, but it's so impossible.

08:07.906 --> 08:12.411
Can you at least increase our faith so we can move into the space that you're offering to us?

08:13.452 --> 08:27.888
And Jesus replies, if you have faith the size of a mustard seed, you would say to this mulberry tree, be uprooted and planted in the seed and it would obey you.

08:29.249 --> 08:30.451
And what's he saying here, everybody?

08:32.192 --> 08:37.298
Faith is this humble trust in the power of God.

08:38.818 --> 08:40.820
Hey, forgive your worst enemy.

08:40.860 --> 08:42.902
Well, I can't do that on my own.

08:43.362 --> 08:46.505
Like I can just muster the psychological strength to do it.

08:47.626 --> 09:01.199
But listen, the tiniest bit of trust, of humble trust, little sea, little mustard seed, that's all you need to unleash all the power in the world.

09:02.200 --> 09:05.283
Because faith isn't open as to God.

09:06.244 --> 09:08.146
God who makes the universe

09:08.450 --> 09:26.897
So the tiniest little, look, crack in the carapace, the shell of your own egotism, that the tiniest little crack in that will let in enormous amounts of light, shift the metaphor, will unleash enormous amounts of energy.

09:29.020 --> 09:31.463
The just person will live by faith, right?

09:32.024 --> 09:32.304
Right.

09:33.146 --> 09:36.210
That's what makes your life wonderful and rich worth living.

09:37.922 --> 09:44.109
Okay, but now watch how this teaching of Jesus is juxtaposed to a little story.

09:44.129 --> 09:56.724
I must say for many years, as I meditate on this gospel, it always struck me as a bit puzzling or a bit of a non-sequitur, like, well, how do you get from that statement about faith, the size of a mustard seed to this parable?

09:56.784 --> 09:58.266
Well, listen to the parable.

10:00.128 --> 10:05.074
Who among you would say to your servant who's just come in from plowing and tending the sheep?

10:05.986 --> 10:07.027
Come here immediately.

10:07.047 --> 10:08.269
Take your place at the table.

10:08.809 --> 10:13.095
No, I mean, wouldn't he rather say to him, prepare for me something to eat.

10:13.495 --> 10:16.359
And then after we're all serving, you can eat something.

10:16.379 --> 10:20.083
So he's talking about a master and a servant of some kind.

10:20.644 --> 10:25.070
The servant's been out the field all day, laboring, hot sun.

10:26.191 --> 10:28.594
And after this long day of labor comes in,

10:29.410 --> 10:33.676
Well, wouldn't it be nice if the master were to say, come on, come on.

10:33.716 --> 10:34.517
You've got a hard day to work.

10:34.537 --> 10:37.841
Come sit here and let me reward you with a nice meal.

10:38.863 --> 10:40.785
No, no, no, since this is a story.

10:41.827 --> 10:43.629
No, you've been working out there in the field all day.

10:43.689 --> 10:44.510
All right, now come in.

10:44.611 --> 10:46.133
It's now your turn to work inside.

10:46.693 --> 10:48.716
Wait on table and serve me and my friends.

10:48.776 --> 10:55.325
And afterwards, something, it seems kind of rough, kind of unfair.

10:56.086 --> 10:58.930
Shouldn't you give this guy a little reward?

11:00.258 --> 11:00.678
Why not?

11:02.220 --> 11:07.847
When you've done all you've been commanded, say, we are unprofitable servants.

11:07.867 --> 11:09.649
We have done what we are obliged to do.

11:10.910 --> 11:12.292
Now, here's the point.

11:12.312 --> 11:14.814
I think then you'll see how it's connected to the first statement.

11:16.356 --> 11:21.923
What's being urged here, everybody, is the stance of humble service.

11:23.284 --> 11:28.530
In our egotism, we think God owes us an explanation.

11:29.474 --> 11:31.877
God owes us some reward.

11:32.138 --> 11:33.480
Hey, yeah, I've been at this all day.

11:33.540 --> 11:35.082
I've been serving you Lord all day.

11:35.102 --> 11:36.083
I've been doing your will.

11:36.524 --> 11:38.327
Don't I get a little something in return?

11:39.208 --> 11:41.431
See, if I'm in that space, where am I?

11:41.972 --> 11:50.344
I'm still in that little tiny egocentric world where I'm expecting recognition, reward, acknowledgement.

11:52.006 --> 11:53.829
Spiritly speaking, that's a waste of time.

11:55.771 --> 11:57.554
The humble person is the one who says,

11:57.858 --> 12:02.083
No, Lord, I exist to serve you.

12:02.143 --> 12:07.870
And in fact, in serving you who need nothing.

12:08.030 --> 12:12.054
Remember, I've told you that many times, everybody, and it's very, very important in this spiritual order.

12:12.515 --> 12:16.900
If we think God needs something from us, then we're all gonna be playing this silly game.

12:17.841 --> 12:25.650
God doesn't need anything from us, which is why serving Him lifts us up.

12:26.114 --> 12:28.418
and makes us more alive.

12:30.102 --> 12:32.506
Don't think of it as I'm laboring in the hot sun.

12:32.526 --> 12:32.827
Think of it.

12:32.887 --> 12:43.207
No, by obeying you, Lord, by doing what you want, by breaking out of this little narrow space of my egotism, I now live for the first time.

12:43.247 --> 12:46.494
The just man will live by faith.

12:47.135 --> 12:47.475
Right.

12:48.317 --> 12:48.818
Right.

12:49.666 --> 12:57.579
Break out of this little narrow space where you're playing games with the ego and recognition and who deserves more.

12:57.639 --> 13:02.526
If you're serving God in that way, you're not in the right space.

13:03.468 --> 13:06.813
You're still in a kind of servile relationship to God.

13:07.875 --> 13:08.736
But what did Jesus say?

13:08.776 --> 13:13.223
I no longer call you servants, but friends.

13:14.025 --> 13:15.006
That's what God wants.

13:15.868 --> 13:17.330
That's what's

13:17.762 --> 13:22.206
enlivening to us spiritually when we become the friends of God.

13:23.167 --> 13:25.249
Now, link these two things together.

13:26.571 --> 13:27.712
Increase our faith.

13:28.432 --> 13:32.837
If you had the faith of a mustard seed, you'd have all the power in the world.

13:33.778 --> 13:34.538
What's faith?

13:35.179 --> 13:37.081
It's breaking out of egotism.

13:38.663 --> 13:46.290
It's trusting in the power and the love and the plan and the project of God for us.

13:46.402 --> 13:52.289
It's surrendering to God's purpose that we might really be alive.

13:52.410 --> 13:56.455
That's where power comes from, where's where light comes from.

13:58.798 --> 14:06.488
Humility, everybody, and faith are urged upon us by all the spiritual masters.

14:07.769 --> 14:10.533
Bernard was asked, what are the three greatest virtues?

14:10.593 --> 14:14.738
He said, humility toss, humility toss, and humility toss.

14:17.378 --> 14:20.141
Thomas Aquinas, what opens the door to the spiritual life?

14:20.522 --> 14:22.064
Faith, faith.

14:23.426 --> 14:26.069
The Bible, without faith, we can't be pleasing to God.

14:26.409 --> 14:27.411
Right, right.

14:29.313 --> 14:36.802
Faith, everybody, is the way in a trusting surrender to the love, purpose, and plan of God.

14:38.284 --> 14:38.865
And God bless you.

14:42.489 --> 14:46.194
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron,

14:46.402 --> 14:51.570
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.

